		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES Styled Pixel Art</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey its been awhile! The engine has been tweaked a lot and changes are still being made, mainly stress and lag related stuff. I've been doing more tile sets and recently went back to address the palette issue. The two main things I'm aiming for is the two players to have contrasting colors. The second thing was addressing Juanias skin color issue. Here's a test of that:<br /><br /><img src="https://40.media.tumblr.com/f7ba99f61b48ea69879e0f29cf8f72dd/tumblr_nmeljktjqM1s4ro4eo1_1280.png" alt="Image" /><br />I also played with the idea of them being pink and blue:<br /><img src="http://puu.sh/h1k9v/a3456629b0.png" alt="Image" /><br />A new tileset in the works:<br /><img src="http://puu.sh/h4bE2/7f2a372701.png" alt="Image" /><br />With this tile set, you can see a slighter greater push for the western style design within the game, mainly a bordertown between Latin America and Native America. <br /><br />Besides that, the main thing going on right now is making sure all of the connecting levels will work under stress tests and building up more levels. Once there's enough gimmicks programmed in, I'd like to make a teaser video (right now most of the levels are just empty levels without enemies or gimmicks).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


